The paper deals with proof complexity, which is a subfield of computational complexity theory. The paper specifically focuses on the space and length of resolution proofs, which falls under the category of proof complexity. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves logical reasoning and deduction, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper's discussion of satisfiability algorithms and clause learning could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's discussion of lower bounds and trade-offs could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
